 "awd_abstract_narration": "Gary, Dale  AST  9618538      The Owens Valley Radio Observatory (OVRO) Solar Array  provides a unique capability for  imaging and spectroscopy in a broad range of microwave  frequencies.  The array will be used by  investigators at a number of institutions to study the  physical parameters of the solar atmosphere,  with particular attention to conditions in active regions  and the temporal and spatial development  of solar flares.  During the grant period, the facility will  be upgraded to include two new  antennas which will effectively double the baseline for  imaging and double the spatial resolution  in the east-west direction.  Upgrades to the data  acquisition system will increase observing time  by 40% and provide a more responsive analysis system for  users, including those accessing data  remotely.  ***",
